Description: Hi. For auction is my Eric Johnson Fender Signature Strat. I have enjoyed it immensely but simply have accumulated too many musical toys so I am thinning the herd. It is exactly as it came from the factory; no alterations, no modifications, never taken apart. This is important to me, I think if EJ and Fender wanted this guitar differently than what it is they would have made it that way. It has been in my smoke free home it's entire life and is easily one of the best examples of a used Strat you'll find. There are no dents, dings or paint chips of any kind. Any scratches present are indistinguishable and can only be seen if looked for in light while tilting the guitar. The neck action is exactly what you would expect...fast. It comes with everything from the factory as seen in the pictures. The wah bar has never been screwed into the guitar nor has it ever had a guitar strap on it, no "buckle rash" or strap marks. It has a new set of EJ strings on it and is ready to play. In an effort provide good pictures I took photos of it both inside and outside. Feel free to ask any questions. When shipped I will wrap the case with bubble wrap top to bottom and box it appropriately. Thanks Shipping and sale to lower 48 only. No international shipping. Not exactly sure what the UPC code is on the listing - that was not added by me. I have this listed for sale locally, if sold locally I reserve the right to stop the auction at that time. Thanks
Title: Eric Johnson Fender Stratocaster Excellent Condition
